ADDITIONAL TERMS FOR HEALTHCARE USE:

This software is designed for healthcare interoperability purposes. Users are 
responsible for:

1. Ensuring compliance with local healthcare regulations (e.g., HIPAA, GDPR, 
   India's Personal Data Protection Act)
2. Proper validation of medical coding and terminology mappings
3. Clinical oversight of any diagnoses or medical decisions
4. Security of patient health information (PHI)

The software includes demonstration data and should not be used for actual 
patient care without proper clinical validation and regulatory approval.

---

ACKNOWLEDGMENTS:

This project supports the digital transformation initiative of the Ministry of 
AYUSH, Government of India, and the World Health Organization's efforts to 
integrate traditional medicine into the global ICD-11 classification system.
